  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Shipping & Logistics Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary: </strong></p><p>We are seeking a highly organized and detail-oriented <strong>Shipping and Logistics Coordinator </strong>to coordinate and provide administrative support within the shipping and logistics department. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in logistics administration, understanding of shipping processes, and the ability to handle documentation, inventory, and shipping coordination.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br /><br /><strong>1. Documentation & Reporting</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare delivery order, labels & examine packing list.</li><li>Maintain accurate records of logistics activities.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>2. Inbound & Outbound Logistics</strong></p><ul><li>Coordinate and manage daily delivery flow, ensuring timely receipt and dispatch of goods.</li><li>Liaise with suppliers, freight forwarders, and transport companies for delivery scheduling.</li><li>Verify incoming and outgoing shipment documents and ensure accuracy.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>3. Inventory Management</strong></p><ul><li>Checking sufficient inventory for delivery of the day.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>4. Order Fulfilment</strong></p><ul><li>Process and fulfil internal and external customer orders promptly and accurately.</li><li>Coordinate with the sales and customer service teams to meet delivery expectations.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>5. Compliance & Safety</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in audits and ensure all logistics processes align with regulatory requirements.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>6. Continuous Improvement</strong></p><ul><li>Identify opportunities to improve logistics processes for cost savings and efficiency.</li><li>Assist in implementing new systems or procedures to enhance logistics operations.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>7. Other Duties</strong></p><ul><li>Support general administrative tasks related to the logistics department.</li><li>Participate in ad-hoc projects or duties as assigned by the management.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or in related field.</li><li>Proven experience as an Logistics Assistant, Administrative Assistant, or similar role is a plus.</li><li>Proficiency in MS Office (Word, Excel) is a plus.</li><li>Excellent organizational, time-management, and multitasking skills.</li><li>Strong communication skills, both verbal and written.</li><li>Work as a Team.</li><li>Attention to detail and ability to work independently.</li></ul>",
